trans-unit.source: Represents a hierarchical collection that can be enumerated with an <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> interface.
Collections that implement the IHierarchicalEnumerable interface are used by ASP.NET site navigation and data source controls.

The IHierarchicalEnumerable interface extends the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable> interface and exposes <xref:System.Web.UI.IHierarchicalEnumerable.GetHierarchyData%2A>, which is a method used to retrieve an <xref:System.Web.UI.IHierarchyData> object from an enumerated item, in addition to the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable.GetEnumerator%2A> method.

Typically, clients that use IHierarchicalEnumerable collections retrieve an <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator> object by calling the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable.GetEnumerator%2A> method, then iterate through the enumeration and call the <xref:System.Web.UI.IHierarchicalEnumerable.GetHierarchyData%2A> on each enumerated item to retrieve an <xref:System.Web.UI.IHierarchyData> object.
Returns a hierarchical data item for the specified enumerated item.

The <xref:System.Object> for which to return an <xref href="System.Web.UI.IHierarchyData"></xref>.
An <xref href="System.Web.UI.IHierarchyData"></xref> instance that represents the <xref:System.Object> passed to the GetHierarchyData method.
